Specification for Multimedia File Usage

Multimedia files in this repository (including musical works, artistic images, Live2D files) do not adhere to the LICENSE, but follow the protocols outlined below:

Authorized Parties
Multimedia file authorization applies only to individuals and non-profit entities and is not applicable to commercial entities.

Authorization Content
The copyright holder hereby grants, free of charge, permanently, and irrevocably, to the authorized party the following:
1. The authorized works are those already present in the "CyanStars" repository or mentioned in the repository on how to obtain multimedia works, including musical works, artistic images, Live2D files, excluding source code (source code follows the specifications in the LICENSE).
2. You are free to download, distribute, use, and create derivative works within the limitations mentioned below.
3. You may showcase the works during live streams or videos alongside gameplay and profit from it.
Usage Restrictions

To protect the rights of the author, you must adhere to the following restrictions when using the works:
1. You may not directly use the works for any commercial purposes.
2. Projects using the works may not be used for profit, except for minor commercial activities intended to offset expenses.
3. You may only use the works in "CyanStars" games, game derivatives, and game promotions and may not be used for other unrelated projects.
4. When creating derivative works related to the "CyanStars" game, you must also comply with laws and community guidelines, follow the same license as described in this document, and refrain from making significant alterations to the works themselves (such as major modifications to artistic images or altering lyrics or melodies of the music).
5. You must provide full attribution to the author of the works in a prominent position.
6. You must add a link to the works in a prominent position.

Disclaimer
The authors and project maintenance team are not liable for any losses or damages incurred by contributors beyond the scope of the license.

---

Multimedia File Contribution Guidelines

Thank you very much for your interest in contributing. If your contributions to this repository include multimedia files, to ensure better regulation of the use of your contributions by maintainers and community members, you also need to adhere to these guidelines:
1. You have confirmed that this work does not conflict with any third-party agreements (such as exclusive or proprietary licenses).
2. You, as the copyright holder, or with permission from the copyright holder, are contributing.
3. You confirm that your contribution will not infringe upon any third-party intellectual property rights or other legal rights and accept the consequences of any resulting losses.

The scope of authorization for your contribution and the restrictions on the authorized party are the same as described in the "Specification for Multimedia File Usage" above.
